exercise.statement:
       {{#scenario}}
           {{#phrasing1}}


                   {{name}} took out a short term small business loan of {{loan_amount}}. The loan accrues simple interest at an annual interest rate of {{yearly_rate}}%, and the time period of the loan is {{months}} months. {{name}} plans to pay the loan back all at once at the end of the {{months}} months.


How much interest does the loan generate over the {{months}} months? 

How much will {{name}} have to pay off at the end of the loan?


           {{/phrasing1}}

           {{#phrasing2}}


                   {{name}} recently had some financial trouble, and as a result they had to borrow {{loan_amount}} in the form of a simple interest loan with an annual interest rate of {{yearly_rate}}%. They plan to pay the loan off in one large payment after {{months}} months.


How much interest does the loan generate over the {{months}} months? 

How much will {{name}} have to pay off at the end of the loan?


           {{/phrasing2}}

           {{#phrasing3}}


                   {{name}} loaned their friend {{loan_amount}}. To make it easier on both of them, it is a simple interest loan with an annual interest rate of {{yearly_rate}}%. After {{months}} months have passed, they expect their friend to pay the loan back in one large payment.


How much interest does the loan generate over the {{months}} months? 

How much will {{name}}'s friend have to pay at the end of the loan?


           {{/phrasing3}}
       {{/scenario}}
